description:
For an international project in Chennai, we are urgently looking for a Power BI developer. The Power BI Developer will analyze, design and build all the reports for the business users. The developer will ensure that he/ she works closely with the business users to document the reporting/ dashboarding requirements and create these reports.










 We are looking for a motivated contractor. Candidates need to be fluent in English.










**Tasks and responsibilities:** 



* Understand the existing system and the reporting requirements;
* Create Reporting and Dashboarding requirements document and validate the same with the business and other stakeholders;
* Estimate the work involved and the schedule for designing, building, testing and deploying these new reports using Power BI;
* Work with the various stakeholders as part of the project and align well to the project objectives and timelines;
* Design the reports and dashboard requirements based on the data model of the application being built;
* Validate the design of the reports and dashboards with both the business users and other stakeholders including the development team;
* Architect and optimize environments with Power BI Suite following the best industry practices
* Install, configure, and manage Power BI Suite as required for the project;
* Conduct training sessions for teams as required;
* Create training material and other project documents as required for the project;
* Build the reports and dashboards and test the same for accuracy, correctness;
* Provide support to the testing team and other stakeholders who test the reports and dashboards (during different phases like System Testing, System Integration Testing, UAT etc.);
* Interact with business unit application owners to resolve performance and end\\-user issues;









**Profile:** 



* Bachelor or Master degree;
* \\+5/\\+7 years of experience in Power BI development;
* Expert knowledge of Power BI platform;
* Knowledge of Azure Cloud platform;
* Very good experience in estimation techniques for reports build, analysis, design, build, test and deploy activities for reports/ dashboards;
* Good knowledge of various data model concepts and performance tuning of queries;
* Ability to use collaborative skills to work with application managers, database administrators, system administrators, and other stakeholders;
* Good listening and communication skills in order to surface issues related to the project;
* Good understanding of technology environment, such as Azure, Azure SQL, MSSQL;
* Proficiency in developing, troubleshooting complex SQL;
* Microsoft Certified: Power BI Data Analyst Associate is an advantage;
* Experience of having worked in an Enterprise Data Wearhouse project is an advantage;
* Understanding of Data Governance process and ability to identify data quality issues is an advantage;
* Fluent in English;
